inference:
Let $E$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $D$ to $\overline{BC}.$ 

[asy]
unitsize(1.5cm);
pair A,B,C,D,E;
A=(0,1);
B=(-1,0);
C=(1,0);
D=(0,0);
E=(0,0);
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--D);
draw(D--E);
label("$A$",A,N);
label("$B$",B,SW);
label("$C$",C,SE);
label("$D$",D,S);
label("$E$",E,S);
label("$45^\circ$",(0.2,0.1));
[/asy]

Since $\overline{AD}$ is a median, $BD = CD.$  Also, $\angle BDE = \angle CDE = 90^\circ,$ so triangles $BDE$ and $CDE$ are congruent by SAS.  Hence, $BE = CE.$

Then
\[\cot B = \frac{BE}{DE} = \frac{CE}{DE} = \cot C,\]so $|\cot B - \cot C| = \boxed{0}.$

ground_truth:
Let $P$ be the foot of the altitude from $A$ to $\overline{BC}.$  Let $x = BD = CD,$ and let $y = BP.$  Since $\angle ADP = 45^\circ,$ $AP = PD = x + y.$

[asy]
unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, C ,D, P;

D = (0,0);
B = (-1,0);
C = (1,0);
A = D + 2*dir(135);
P = (A.x,0);

draw(A--P--C--cycle);
draw(A--B);
draw(A--D);

label("$A$", A, NW);
label("$B$", B, S);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$P$", P, SW);
label("$x$", (B + D)/2, S, red);
label("$x$", (C + D)/2, S, red);
label("$y$", (B + P)/2, S, red);
label("$x + y$", (A + P)/2, W, red);
[/asy]

Then
\[\cot B = -\cot \angle ABP = -\frac{y}{x + y},\]and
\[\cot C = \frac{2x + y}{x + y}.\]Hence,
\[|\cot B - \cot C| = \left| -\frac{2x + 2y}{x + y} \right| = \boxed{2}.\]

